**W1-D3-Instance_Methods_Student**
Goal: Same pattern as before, formal name now — instance methods that make decisions using an object's own data. Django model methods work exactly this way.

```python
class Student:
    def __init__(self, name, marks):
        self.name = name
        self.marks = marks

    def average(self):
        return sum(self.marks) / len(self.marks)

    def result(self):
        avg = self.average()
        if avg >= 40:
            return "Pass"
        else:
            return "Fail"

s1 = Student("Ravi", [80, 45, 60])
s2 = Student("Sai", [30, 25, 35])

print(s1.name, "->", s1.result())
print(s2.name, "->", s2.result())
```

